===Verb===

'''to mooch'''  (''intransitive'' or ''transitive'')
# to [[wander]] around [[aimlessly]]
# to [[beg]], [[cadge]] or [[sponge]] (things); to [[exploit]] or [[take advantage]] of others for personal gain
# to [[sap]] information off of others

e.g., Bret mooched off Terry for the upcoming Social Studies Test

===Noun===

'''moochment'''

# the act of mooching

e.g., "Jonathan!" Bret exclaimed. "Moochment is outlawed at school!"


'''moochery'''

# A person, place, or thing, from which one mooches off of

e.g., In our case, Nick was the moochery, for he told Mark about the Science exam.

'''moochist'''

# A repeated offender of moochment

# One who mooches; all definitions apply

